column168: XPO Logistics terminal NCS experienced a UN3267 Ferrogard 903 release from a 5-gallon poly pail. ERTS dispatched contractors to conduct cleanup operations. Contractors arrived onsite and confirmed approximately 5-gallons of product released to a 5’ x 16’ area of the trailer floor due to a puncture. Absorbents were deployed and worked into the impacted area. The damaged pail, impacted absorbents, debris, and PPE were then containerized into a 55-gallon poly drum. The waste was staged onsite for terminal personnel to manage.
